Package io.artframework.parser.flow

Class FlowLineParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.artframework.parser.LineParser<ArtObjectContext<?>>
      • io.artframework.parser.flow.FlowLineParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Scoped, java.util.Iterator<java.lang.String>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ArtObjectContextLineParser
    public abstract class FlowLineParser
extends LineParser<ArtObjectContext<?>>
implements Scoped
    The flow line parser takes a single String (line) and parses it into an art object context.

    You can provide your own flow parsers by implementing this interface and registering it with the FlowLineParserProvider in the OnBootstrap phase.

    This is useful if you added new ArtObjects and need to provide a way to parse the corresponding ArtObjectContext from an input.
